  "sensitivityAnalysisDetail": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/sa/pedicle-screw-sa-01",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Material property and contact stiffness sensitivity analysis for non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analyses were performed varying titanium alloy elastic modulus (±10%), yield strength (±15%), UHMWPE block modulus (±20%), and screw-rod interface contact stiffness (±30%). Construct stiffness QoI varied by at most 4.2% across the full parameter space; yield force QoI showed maximum sensitivity to Ti-6Al-4V yield strength (6.8% change per 15% input perturbation), confirming that material property uncertainty is the dominant contributor to model output variability and that the <10% acceptance bound remains robust."
  },
